title: Auburn to Start Sean White Against Kentucky
text:
Auburn to Start Sean White Against Kentucky Tools By Alabama News Network 
Story Created: Oct 15, 2015 at 4:05 PM CDT 
MONTGOMERY, AL --- Sources tell Alabama News Network sports reporter Christina Chambers that Sean White will start for Auburn against the Kentucky Wildcats. 


Auburn coach Gus Malzahn opened up the quarterback battle between Sean White and former starter Jeremy Johnson during the bye week. 
White has two starts under his belt this season. He's completed 26 of his 38 passes for 296 yards. He has no touchdown passes and one interception. 
Johnson began the season as the starting quarterback, but was benched after a slow start. He has completed 43 of 72 passes for 473 yards this season with 5 touchdowns and 6 interceptions.
